.BR strnlen ()
looks only all up in tha first
.I maxlen
bytes at
.I s
and never beyond
.IR s+maxlen .
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR strnlen ()
function returns
.IR strlen(s) ,
if dat is less than
.IR maxlen ,
or
.I maxlen
if there is no null byte (\(aq\\0\(aq) among tha first
.I maxlen
bytes pointed ta by
.IR s .
